description: Starlight dances along the hinged wooden rails of this small, portable pen that has been situated on a slightly bumpy knoll of grass and dirt in the meadow.  Gnawed bits of rope dangle from equally gnawed planks, and several rusty cow bells, battered and dented, hang along the perimeter rails.  A rickety upturned box and a teeth-marked tin pail are underneath a handpainted sign that reads, "Gynny."
